  "html": "\n<div><center>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td><font><img src=\"../images/R.gif\"/> <strong>Princess\n        Volupine</strong></font><hr noshade=\"\"/>\n<p><font>Volupine, from <em>voluptas </em>and\n        \"pine,\" is the personification of Venice, who\n        is traditionally represented in poetry as a woman. Eliot\n        suitably names her \"decaying beauty.\" Princess\n        is, among others, a euphemism for whore.</font></p>\n<p><font><em>reference topics</em></font></p>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td>Princess Volupine and \"Burbank\"</td>\n<td><a href=\"Portrait175_JJ.htm\"><font><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></font></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>A Beautiful Dream</td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank.htm\"><font><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></font></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>structural analysis</td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank.htm\"><font><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></font></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><font>back to \"Burbank\" </font></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><font><img src=\"../images/arrowry.gif\"/></font></a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</center></div>\n",
  "text": "Princess Volupine Volupine, from voluptas and \"pine,\" is the personification of Venice, who is traditionally represented in poetry as a woman. Eliot suitably names her \"decaying beauty.\" Princess is, among others, a euphemism for whore. reference topics Princess Volupine and \"Burbank\" A Beautiful Dream structural analysis back to \"Burbank\"",
